---
alwaysApply: true
---

A change is not complete when code is written.
A change is complete only when it is verified to the extent possible in scope.

After edits:
- run the smallest relevant checks available
- review the diff for unrelated changes
- state what was verified
- state what was not verified
- state any remaining assumptions or risk

Prefer targeted verification:
- relevant tests first
- build/typecheck/lint as appropriate
- behavior notes for the exact flow changed
- nearby regression checks for affected core loop surfaces

If you cannot verify a critical assumption, do not present the work as settled.
Say what is still unknown and what needs inspection.
Stop instead of guessing.
